<h1>Connect two Nodes through fuzzy coupling</h1>

<%= form_tag 'do_connect' do %>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="small-3 columns">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="small-3 columns">
            <label for="right-label" class="right inline">Node 1</label>
          </div>
          <div class="small-9 columns">
            <select name="neoServer1">
              <% @neo_servers.each do |neo| %>
                  <option value="<%= neo['server']['data']['id'] %>"><%= neo['server']['data']['name'] %></option>
              <% end %>
            </select>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="small-2 columns">
        <div class="row collapse prefix-radius">
          <div class="small-6 columns">
            <span class="prefix">Tightly Coupling:</span>
          </div>
          <div class="small-6 columns">
            <%= number_field_tag 'tight_coupling', nil, :step => 0.05, :in => 0..1 %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="small-2 columns">
        <div class="row collapse prefix-radius">
          <div class="small-6 columns">
            <span class="prefix">Loosely Coupling:</span>
          </div>
          <div class="small-6 columns">
            <%= number_field_tag 'loose_coupling', nil, :step => 0.05, :in => 0..1 %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="small-3 columns">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="small-3 columns">
            <label for="right-label" class="right inline">Node 2</label>
          </div>
          <div class="small-9 columns">
            <select name="neoServer2">
              <% @neo_servers.each do |neo| %>
                  <option value="<%= neo['server']['data']['id'] %>"><%= neo['server']['data']['name'] %></option>
              <% end %>
            </select>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="small-2 columns">
        <%= submit_tag 'Submit', class: 'button postfix' %>
      </div>
    </div>
<% end %>

<div class="panel"><p>The <span class="bold">tightly coupling</span> measurement can be seen as an indicator of risk resulting from the tight connection between two components.
  If one of two tightly coupled components fails, the dependent one will not function properly either.</p>
  <p><span class="bold">Loosely coupling</span> includes the components' resilience  and mitigation into the evaluation.</p>
</div>
<br>
